  ">Rank< is nae so important t' >bards< as it is t' others," says Adaon.  
"It is really only used as a rough determination o' when y'r elders 
teach ye new skills.  We don't put much emphasis on it, as far as 
guild >politics< goes, though.
  "There be fifteen ranks o' bards.  In order, they are Probationer, 
Fochlucan, Rhymer, MacFuirmidh, Doss, Lyrist, Canaith, Troubador, 
Sonateer, Cli, Anstruth, Muse, Racaraide, Ollamh, and Magna 
Alumnae.
  "Some outsiders are often befuddled by our titles, when they are 
actually some of the most elegant and clear expressions of who we 
are.  They are nae just an indication to other >bards< of our >rank<, 
but also an indication to outsiders of our standing in the world.  We 
ha' adopted a system of naming that reflects many of our >talents<, so 
that upon the mere mention of a bard's title, those in the know 
immediately recognize his standing.
  "Simple and elegant, like the bards ourselves," concludes Adaon 
with a wink.
